# Shell Sort

## Problem

Shell Sort is an improved version of Insertion Sort that sorts elements far apart first and gradually reduces the gap between elements.

---

# Steps of Shell Sort Algorithm

1. Initialize gap = n/2.
2. Compare elements separated by gap distance.
3. Perform insertion sort for elements in each gap group.
4. Reduce the gap by half.
5. Repeat the process until gap becomes 1.
6. Final array becomes sorted.

---

# Pseudo Code

BEGIN

INPUT array A
INPUT n

FOR gap = n/2 TO gap > 0
    gap = gap/2

    FOR i = gap TO n-1

        temp = A[i]
        j = i

        WHILE j >= gap AND A[j-gap] > temp

            A[j] = A[j-gap]
            j = j-gap

        ENDWHILE

        A[j] = temp

    ENDFOR

ENDFOR

PRINT sorted array

END

---

# Time Complexity

| Case       | Complexity |
| ---------- | ---------- |
| Best Case  | O(n log n) |
| Worst Case | O(n²)      |

---

# Space Complexity
O(1)
---

# Important Exam Points

* Shell Sort is based on Insertion Sort.
* It sorts distant elements first.
* Gap value decreases gradually.
* It is an in-place sorting algorithm.
* It is not a stable sorting algorithm.
